## Part 5: Hero & UX Flow Recommendations

### Navigation Architecture

**Current implementation**:
- **Bottom floating dock**: 6 icon items (Home, Work, Lab, Stack, Writing, Agent)
- **Header**: Avatar (top-left) + Social links (top-right, including GitHub)
- **No sidebar**: Clean, spacious content area

### Navigation Philosophy: Hero-First Discovery

**The insight**: In the first 30 seconds, visitors navigate through CONTENT, not through nav bars. The dock is for returning visitors and deep navigation; new visitors discover through hero content.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [Avatar]                              [GitHub · LinkedIn · X]   │
│                                                                 │
│                                                                 │
│                    ION MESCA                                    │
│                    Lead Product Designer                        │
│                                                                 │
│        Building AI products at Ledgy. Ships code with Claude.   │
│        10+ years · AI Products · Fintech Systems                │
│                                                                 │
│                                                                 │
│        FEATURED WORK (the primary discovery surface)            │
│        ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐         │
│        │ [Project 1] │ │ [Project 2] │ │ [Project 3] │         │
│        │ +40% metric │ │ -35% time   │ │ 10K users   │         │
│        └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘         │
│                                                                 │
│        Quick Links: Lab Experiments · Chat with Agent           │
│                                                                 │
│                                                                 │
│         ─────────────────────────────────────────────           │
│         [Home] [Work] [Lab] [Stack] [Writing] [Agent]           │
│                    (bottom floating dock)                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Why hero-first works**:
1. **Recruiters scan content, not nav bars** — Featured work cards with metrics give instant talking points
2. **GitHub visible on every page** — Satisfies xAI's "technical signals immediately" requirement
3. **Bottom dock is mobile-native** — Matches iOS/Android tab bar patterns, thumb-friendly
4. **Navigation gets out of the way** — Content area feels spacious, not cramped

### The 30-Second Hero

**Key elements** (in order of visual priority):
1. **Name + title immediately** — No mystery, no scrolling required
2. **Proof chips** — "10+ years" · "AI Products" · "Fintech Systems" · "Ships code"
3. **Featured work grid** — 2-3 project cards with outcome metrics visible
4. **Quick links** — Lab Experiments, Chat with Agent (secondary CTAs)

**Anti-patterns to avoid**:
- Nav bar as primary discovery (dock is for deep navigation, not first impression)
- Photo taking up hero space
- "I'm passionate about..." (show, don't tell)
- Live API dependencies (hero must load instantly)

### Mobile Consideration

Most recruiter first-looks happen on mobile. Your hero MUST work on mobile:
- **Thumb-friendly**: Featured work cards have large tap targets
- **Bottom dock**: Natural mobile pattern, no hamburger menu
- **GitHub in header**: Always visible, satisfies technical reviewers on first scroll
- **Featured work above fold**: Metrics visible without scrolling on mobile

### GitHub Visibility

> [!note] Technical Credibility Solved
> GitHub is now visible in the header on EVERY page (top-right social links). This satisfies:
> - Anthropic: "GitHub profile or personal projects" requirement
> - xAI: "Technical depth discoverable within 1-2 clicks"
>
> No need for a separate "GitHub link prominently on home page" — it's always there.

