## Part 6: Differentiation Strategy

### What Makes You Non-Generic

| Typical Designer | You |
|-----------------|-----|
| "I design AI products" | "I build AI agents that ship to production" |
| "I prototype in Figma" | "I ship PRs with Claude Code" |
| "I understand fintech" | "I designed IFRS 2-compliant systems" |
| "I'm a leader" | "I built a design team from 0 at a Sequoia company" |

### How to Signal This Without Being Arrogant

**Don't**: "I'm one of the few designers who can code."
**Do**: Show code. Link to GitHub. Have interactive demos. Let the work speak.

**Don't**: "I deeply understand AI."
**Do**: Have an AI agent on your portfolio. Show Claude Code workflows. Use AI terminology correctly in case studies.

**Don't**: "I've worked on complex financial products."
**Do**: Show the regulatory constraints, the edge cases, the systems diagrams. Let complexity be evident.

