### Lab Page Structure

```
/lab

EXPERIMENTS

Interactive demos of things I've built.
Each one ships real code, not just mockups.

┌──────────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────────┐
│ AI FEEDBACK AGENT    │ │ HOW THIS SITE        │
│ [Live demo]          │ │ WAS BUILT            │
│ Try the agent that   │ │ [Live demo]          │
│ processes feedback   │ │ Claude Code workflow │
│ • Claude API         │ │ from prompt to PR    │
│ • n8n               │ │ • Next.js 15         │
└──────────────────────┘ │ • Claude Code        │
                        └──────────────────────┘
```

### The "How This Site Was Built" Demo

This is your secret weapon for Anthropic. It's meta but powerful:
- Show actual prompts you used to build the portfolio
- Show the code they generated
- Show your iteration process
- Make it interactive (visitors can see different prompts)

This answers "can this person work with Claude Code?" without you having to claim it.

