## Part 15: Critical Issues Addressed

Summary of risks identified and how this plan addresses them:

| Issue | Risk Level | Resolution |
|-------|-----------|------------|
| Hero live API dependency | Critical | Static hero with CTA to agent page; no live API calls on load |
| AI over-indexing | Critical | Domain tags instead of "AI designer"; Block/Ramp sections emphasize fintech + leadership |
| xAI technical-first path | High | GitHub visible in header on EVERY page; Layer 3 collapsibles within 1-2 clicks |
| Tabs hide content | High | **Replaced with scrollytelling** — 6-section structure with sticky rail + scroll sync |
| Problem-first case studies | High | **Replaced with results-first hero** — Outcomes above fold, story below |
| Sidebar navigation | Medium | **Replaced with bottom dock** — Hero-first discovery, dock for deep navigation |
| Lab/Agent gimmick risk | High | Explicit quality bar; "Option C: skip for v1" acknowledged |
| Company names as posturing | Medium | Use domain tags ("AI Products · Fintech Systems") not company names |
| NDA mechanism missing | Medium | Private deck + password system documented |
| Evidence staleness | Medium | AI-generated PDF solution; potential hero project |

### Key Architecture Decisions (January 2026)

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Bottom floating dock** | Mobile-native, gets out of the way, hero-first discovery |
| **No sidebar** | Clean content area, spacious feel, dock handles navigation |
| **Results-first hero** | Creates curiosity ("How did they achieve that?"), gives recruiters instant talking points |
| **6-section scrollytelling** | Problem → Constraints → Approach → System → Use Cases → Results |
| **Layer 3 inside Section 04** | Technical depth collapsible within System section, not a separate tab |
| **GitHub in header** | Visible on every page, satisfies xAI technical-first requirement |

